From: claude[bot] <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Methodology improvements for 2026-05-17 (workflow fixes)

The auto-improve workflow's GitHub App token does not carry `workflows`
permission, so it cannot push edits under .github/workflows/. Verified
again today: `git push` was rejected with

    ! [remote rejected]   improve/2026-05-17 -> improve/2026-05-17
      (refusing to allow a GitHub App to create or update workflow
       `.github/workflows/2h-bluesky.yml` without `workflows` permission)

If you are a maintainer with `workflows: write`, apply this patch
manually with:

    git checkout improve/2026-05-17
    git apply improve-2026-05-17-workflow-fixes.patch
    git add .github/workflows/
    git commit -m "Apply 2026-05-17 RSS + Bluesky pipeline fixes"
    git push

This is the sixth consecutive iteration of the same fix (see
improve/2026-05-12, /2026-05-13, /2026-05-14, /2026-05-16, today). The
single most valuable follow-up is granting the daily-improve App
`workflows: write` so it self-applies. Context for what this fixes:
see IMPROVEMENTS.md.

Verification done from inside the runner today (2026-05-17):
- 22 RSS feed URLs in the patch all return HTTP 200 with valid feed
  bodies AND fresh content within the last 30 days.
- 1 RSS URL (venturebeat.com/category/ai/feed/) returns 200 with a
  valid feed body but the latest item is 2026-01-22 (~4 months stale).
  Kept in the workflow but flagged in the Claude prompt as low-signal.
- 2 Bluesky endpoints (search + author-feed) on the api.bsky.app host
  both return HTTP 200 with valid JSON.
- The legacy URLs being removed all confirmed broken/rotted:
    * ai.meta.com/blog/rss/                  HTTP 400 (header) / 404 (page)
    * googleaiblog.blogspot.com/atom.xml     200 but frozen <updated>=2025-10-07
    * public.api.bsky.app/.../searchPosts    HTTP 403 (BunnyCDN)
    * blogs.microsoft.com/ai/feed/           200 but frozen <pubDate>=2022-12-06

NEW vs the improve/2026-05-16 patch:
- Routes Microsoft AI coverage to news.microsoft.com/source/topics/ai/feed/
  (last item 2026-05-14) AND microsoft.com/en-us/research/blog/feed/
  (last item 2026-05-15) instead of blogs.microsoft.com/ai/feed/
  (frozen at 2022-12-06). Yesterday's patch would have wired up a
  3.5-year-stale feed.
- Replaces lesswrong.com/feed.xml with chinatalk.media/feed —
  ChinaTalk (Jordan Schneider) is more directly relevant to the AI-news
  beat than LessWrong's broader rationalist content, particularly with
  the running Trump–Xi summit + H200-clearance + DeepSeek V4 threads.

